@prefix : <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#> .
@prefix bfo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/> .
@prefix cco: <https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

bfo:BFO_0000050 a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Plans are part_of Charters (scope containment)."@en .

dcterms:created a owl:AnnotationProperty .

dcterms:creator a owl:AnnotationProperty .

dcterms:modified a owl:AnnotationProperty .

dcterms:title a owl:AnnotationProperty .

xsd:date a rdfs:Datatype .

skos:definition a owl:AnnotationProperty .

<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4> a owl:Ontology ;
    rdfs:label "CCO Extension for Intention Information Entities" ;
    dcterms:created "2025-01-21"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:creator "Darrion Burgess" ;
    dcterms:modified "2026-04-12"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:title "CCO Extension for Intention Information Entities" ;
    rdfs:comment """A disciplined extension to the Common Core Ontologies (CCO) for modeling
intentional planning and execution.

This ontology fills genuine gaps in CCO's coverage of intention information entities:
- Charter: A Prescriptive ICE declaring scope of directed concern (CCO has Plan and Objective but no scope class)
- inServiceOf: A teleological relation linking Prescriptive ICEs to the Objectives they serve (CCO lacks this)

CCO modules imported (via owl:imports):
- InformationEntityOntology: Prescriptive ICE (ont00000965), Event Status Nominal ICE (ont00000203), prescribes (ont00001942), is_measured_by_nominal (ont00001868)
- AgentOntology: Plan (ont00000974), Objective (ont00000476)
- EventOntology: Planned Act (ont00000228), Act (ont00000832)

Transitively available via CCO import chain:
- ExtendedRelationOntology: is_successor_of (ont00001775)
- TimeOntology, GeospatialOntology, BFO 2020

InformationEntityOntology is imported directly (not just transitively) because Prescriptive ICE
(ont00000965) is the foundational parent class for Charter, Context, Plan, and Objective —
all core vocabulary classes. Making this dependency explicit ensures Protégé resolves it
correctly without relying on transitive catalog lookups.

Local resolution: see catalog-v001.xml for IRI → local file mappings.
For full CCO definitions, see: https://github.com/CommonCoreOntology/CommonCoreOntologies
For design rationale, see: V4_DESIGN.md"""@en ;
    owl:imports cco:AgentOntology,
        cco:EventOntology,
        cco:InformationEntityOntology ;
    owl:versionIRI <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4/4.3.0> ;
    owl:versionInfo "4.3.0" .

:AgentContextType a owl:NamedIndividual,
        :ContextType ;
    rdfs:label "Agent Context Type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "People required for execution. DSL syntax: +@bob, +@manager. Maps to CCO Agent."@en .

:Blocked a owl:NamedIndividual,
        cco:ont00000203 ;
    rdfs:label "Blocked"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The Action cannot proceed due to an external dependency or blocker. File format: [=]"@en .

:Cancelled a owl:NamedIndividual,
        cco:ont00000203 ;
    rdfs:label "Cancelled"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The Action was abandoned without completion. Terminal state. File format: [_]"@en .

:CategoryContextType a owl:NamedIndividual,
        :ContextType ;
    rdfs:label "Category Context Type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "General categories or domains. DSL syntax: +work, +personal, +urgent. For organization and filtering."@en .

:Completed a owl:NamedIndividual,
        cco:ont00000203 ;
    rdfs:label "Completed"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The Action finished successfully. Terminal state. File format: [x]"@en .

:FacilityContextType a owl:NamedIndividual,
        :ContextType ;
    rdfs:label "Facility Context Type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Physical locations required for execution. DSL syntax: +@office, +@home. Maps to CCO Facility."@en .

:InProgress a owl:NamedIndividual,
        cco:ont00000203 ;
    rdfs:label "In Progress"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The Action is currently being executed. File format: [-]"@en .

:NotStarted a owl:NamedIndividual,
        cco:ont00000203 ;
    rdfs:label "Not Started"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The Action has not begun execution. File format: [ ]"@en .

:ToolContextType a owl:NamedIndividual,
        :ContextType ;
    rdfs:label "Tool Context Type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Tools, equipment, or software required for execution. DSL syntax: +computer, +phone. Maps to CCO Artifact."@en .

:contextBroader a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "context broader"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Enables tag hierarchies where child contexts inherit from parents. Similar to SKOS broader concept. Example: +neovim contextBroader +terminal contextBroader +computer."@en ;
    rdfs:domain :Context ;
    rdfs:range :Context ;
    owl:inverseOf :contextNarrower ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Context to its parent in the context hierarchy."@en .

:hasAlias a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has alias"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"=\" syntax in the .actions file format. Aliases provide stable references that persist when plan names change. Must be unique within workspace scope."@en ;
    rdfs:domain bfo:BFO_0000001 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Plan to a human-readable alias that can be used for reference."@en .

:hasCompletedDateTime a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has completed date time"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"%\" syntax in the .actions file format. Should only be present when status is Completed."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000228 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf cco:ont00001767 ;
    skos:definition "Relates an Action to the date/time when it was completed."@en .

:hasContextIdentifier a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has context identifier"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps the DSL tag name (e.g., \"work\", \"computer\") to the Context entity. Must be unique within workspace scope."@en ;
    rdfs:domain :Context ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The string identifier used to reference this context in the DSL."@en .

:hasContextType a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has context type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Enables typed contexts for better organization and CCO alignment."@en ;
    rdfs:domain :Context ;
    rdfs:range :ContextType ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Context to its type classification."@en .

:hasCreatedDateTime a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has created date time"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"^\" syntax in the .actions file format. Can be derived from UUIDv7 if not explicitly set."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000974 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf cco:ont00001767 ;
    skos:definition "Relates an entity in the action model to the date/time when it was first created."@en .

:hasDueDateTime a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has due date time"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \":\" syntax in the .actions file format. The deadline by which this act must be done — distinct from hasScheduledDateTime (when the agent plans to do it). For recurring plans, this is computed from the due-recurrence rule during act expansion. Example: garbage is due Monday morning (:), but planned Sunday night (@)."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000228 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf cco:ont00001767 ;
    skos:definition "Relates an Action to the date/time by which it must be completed."@en .

:hasDueRecurrenceRule a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has due recurrence rule"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"R:\" syntax following a \":\" due-date in the .actions file format. When present alongside hasRecurrenceRule, generates independent due-date and scheduled-date streams. Each expanded Action may receive a hasDueDateTime computed from this rule."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000974 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Plan to an RFC 5545 RRULE string defining the recurrence pattern for when acts are due."@en .

:hasDurationMinutes a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has duration minutes"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"D\" syntax in the .actions file format (D60 = 60 minutes). Used for time blocking and capacity planning."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000228 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:integer ;
    skos:definition "Relates an Action to its duration in minutes."@en .

:hasPriority a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has priority"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"!\" syntax in the .actions file format. 1=Urgent+Important, 2=Important+NotUrgent, 3=Urgent+NotImportant, 4=NotUrgent+NotImportant."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000965 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:integer ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Plan to its priority level (1-4, Eisenhower Matrix)."@en .

:hasRecurrenceRule a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has recurrence rule"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"R:\" syntax in the .actions file format. When present, the Plan provides recurrence or schedule semantics that may generate related Actions."@en ;
    rdfs:domain bfo:BFO_0000001 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Plan to an RFC 5545 RRULE string defining recurrence pattern."@en .

:hasScheduledDateTime a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has scheduled date time"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"@\" syntax in the .actions file format. The time the agent intends to perform this act — distinct from hasDueDateTime (when it must be done). For recurring plans, this is computed from the do-recurrence rule during act expansion."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000228 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf cco:ont00001767 ;
    skos:definition "Relates an Action to the date/time when the agent intends to execute it."@en .

:hasSequentialChildren a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has sequential children"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"~\" syntax in the .actions file format. When true, each child Plan implicitly depends on the previous sibling completing."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000974 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
    skos:definition "Indicates whether child Plans should be processed sequentially."@en .

:hasSubCharter a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has sub charter"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A Charter contains another Charter as a sub-scope. Specializes BFO has_part for Charter hierarchy. Example: \"Health\" hasSubCharter \"Fitness\" hasSubCharter \"Gym Training\"."@en ;
    rdfs:domain :Charter ;
    rdfs:range :Charter ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf bfo:BFO_0000051 ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Charter to a Charter that represents a narrower scope of directed concern within it."@en .

:hasUUID a owl:DatatypeProperty,
        owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has UUID"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"#\" syntax in the .actions file format. Provides universal uniqueness across systems and time. UUIDv7 encodes creation timestamp."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000974 ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "Relates an entity in the action model to its unique identifier (UUIDv7 preferred)."@en .

:inServiceOf a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "in service of"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A teleological relation filling a genuine CCO gap: CCO has prescribes (plan→act) but lacks a relation for "this prescriptive entity serves that objective." Domain is Prescriptive ICE so both Plans and Charters can serve Objectives.

Maps to the "*" marker in the .actions file format. A Plan may serve zero objectives (standalone task) or multiple objectives."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000965 ;
    rdfs:range cco:ont00000476 ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Prescriptive Information Content Entity to the Objective it works toward."@en .

:requiresContext a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "requires context"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Maps to the \"+\" syntax in the .actions file format. Context entities enable tag hierarchies and typed contexts (facilities, agents, tools, etc.)."@en ;
    rdfs:domain cco:ont00000965 ;
    rdfs:range :Context ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Plan to a Context entity required for execution."@en .

cco:ont00001775 a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Used for plan dependency ordering. A Plan that is_successor_of another Plan cannot proceed until the predecessor completes. Maps to the \"<\" predecessor syntax in the .actions file format."@en .

cco:ont00001868 a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Links an Action to its Event Status Nominal ICE (lifecycle phase)."@en .

cco:ont00001942 a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Links a Plan to the Actions it prescribes. One Plan can prescribe many Actions."@en .

bfo:BFO_0000051 a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Plan decomposition - parent actions have child actions as parts. Also Charter → Plan containment. Maps to the \">\" children syntax in the .actions file format."@en .

:contextNarrower a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "context narrower"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Inverse of contextBroader. Enables queries to find all child contexts."@en ;
    rdfs:domain :Context ;
    rdfs:range :Context ;
    skos:definition "Relates a Context to its children in the context hierarchy."@en .

cco:ont00000476 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Represents a project or story - the desired outcome that plans work toward. Maps to the \"*\" story/project marker in the .actions file format."@en .

:Charter a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Charter"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A Charter establishes the boundary of responsibility or interest without prescribing specific acts (that's Plan) or target states (that's Objective). It answers "what domain am I responsible for?"

Examples: "Health & Fitness", "Career Development", "Home Maintenance"

Charters contain Plans and Actions (via has_part) and Plans serve Objectives (via inServiceOf). This creates the pipeline: Charter (scope) → Plan (prescription) → Action (execution).

CCO has Plan and Objective but lacks a class for scope-of-concern declarations. Charter fills this genuine gap."""@en ;
    rdfs:subClassOf cco:ont00000965 ;
    skos:definition "A Prescriptive Information Content Entity that declares the scope of directed concern for an agent or organization."@en .

cco:ont00000228 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Action"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Represents an action instance or executable work item. An Action may be prescribed by a Plan or exist directly within a Charter."@en .

cco:ont00000974 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Represents an action definition or task template. Maps to \"Action\" in the .actions file format."@en .

cco:ont00001767 a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Parent property for hasScheduledDateTime, hasDueDateTime, hasCompletedDateTime, hasCreatedDateTime."@en .

:ContextType a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Context Type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Enables typed contexts that can map to specific CCO classes. Examples: facility (@office), agent (@bob), tool (computer)."@en ;
    skos:definition "A classification for Context entities (facility, agent, tool, etc.)."@en .

cco:ont00000203 a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "In this vocabulary: Used for lifecycle status values of Actions (NotStarted, InProgress, Completed, Blocked, Cancelled)."@en .

:Context a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Context"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Context represents execution requirements following Getting Things Done (GTD) methodology. Contexts support hierarchical relationships for tag organization and inheritance. Maps to \"+\" syntax in .actions file format."@en ;
    rdfs:subClassOf cco:ont00000965 ;
    skos:definition "A resource, location, tool, or person required for plan execution (GTD context methodology)."@en .
